CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 18, 1957, page 23, reads: "'The Sisters' - These smiling young ladies have plenty to smile about. They are the members and sponsors of the new YMCA group, the Sequoires Club, which is Spanish for 'The Sisters.' The girls sponsored a get acquainted tea in honor of their mothers recently. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of sixteen women, members of the YMCA Sequoires Club, including: Laura Cooper, Doris Garrett, Joyce Sharpe, Judy White, Carolyn Cannon, Ernestine Robinson, Carol Hatton, Marsha Hord, Rita White, Carol Haywood, Laverne White, Janice White, Lavern Perry, Delilah Wright, Jackie Brown, and Gloria Ramsey, posed in front of brick fireplace and open doorway in interior
